                    <span class="font-medium text-gray-800"
                      >Why do different websites show slightly different T-bill
                      yields?</span
                    >
                    <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">+</span>
                  </button>
                  <div
                    class="px-4 pb-3 hidden faq-answer text-sm text-gray-700"
                  >
                    Differences usually come from:
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-1">
                      <li>Different day-count conventions (360 vs 365 days)</li>
                      <li>
                        Using discount yield vs investment rate vs
                        bond-equivalent yield
                      </li>
                      <li>Rounding of prices, yields, or days to maturity</li>
                      <li>Assumptions about settlement dates and holidays</li>
                    </ul>
                    This calculator lets you control the day-count basis and
