                    >
                    <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">+</span>
                  </button>
                  <div
                    class="px-4 pb-3 hidden faq-answer text-sm text-gray-700"
                  >
                    If you buy a T-bill at auction or in the secondary market
                    and hold it to maturity, your nominal return (difference
                    between purchase price and face value) is known in advance
                    and backed by the issuing government. However, your
                    <em>real</em> return after inflation and taxes is not
